<item>
            <title>[SPR-2578] Spring does not inherit @Transactional correctly when &lt;aop:config target-class-proxy=&quot;true&quot; /&gt;</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-2578</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;According to the documentation (&lt;a href=&quot;http://static.springframework.org/spring/docs/2.0.x/reference/transaction.html#transaction-declarative-annotations&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://static.springframework.org/spring/docs/2.0.x/reference/transaction.html#transaction-declarative-annotations&lt;/a&gt;), Annotating interface &quot;IFoo&quot; using @Transactional is supposed to affect the implementations of implementations of &quot;IFoo&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is the case when using Interface-based proxying, but does not work when using CGLIB proxies.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue is easy to reproduce.. Just take any IFoo, set it @Transactional, create a class that implements IFoo, and use the following in the spring appContext.xml :&lt;/p&gt;

</description>
